quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  19,1,Kaf Ha Ya 'Ayn Sad
  19,2,Recount your Lord's mercy on His servant Zechariah
  19,3,When he called to His Lord silently
  19,4,"he said, \"My Lord, my bones have weakened, and my head shimmers with grey hair, but never, Lord, have I failed to be blessed in praying to you"
  19,5,"And I fear what my kinsfolk [will do] after I am gone. My wife has been barren, so give me an heir as a gift from You"
  19,6,"one who will receive my inheritance and he will be an heir to the family of Jacob. And make him, my Lord, pleasing to You"
  19,7,"O Zechariah, We bring you good news of a son whose name will be John, a name We have never given to anyone else before"
  19,8,"[Zechariah] said, \"My Lord, how will I have a son when my wife has been barren and I have reached advanced old age"
  19,9,"He said, \"It will be so. Your Lord says: 'It is easy for Me, for I created you before, when you were nothing"
  19,10,"[Zechariah] said, \"My Lord, give me a sign.\" He said, \"Your sign is that you will not speak to people for three full nights"
  19,11,"So he came out from the sanctuary and signaled his people to glorify [God] in the morning and in the evening"
  19,12,"John, take hold of the Book with steadfastness.\" And We gave him wisdom [while he was still] a boy"
  19,13,"as well as affection from Us and purity, and he was always mindful of Us"
  19,14,"and full of kindness towards his parents, and he was not domineering or rebellious"
  19,15,"[God's] peace was upon him on the day he was born and the day of his death, and it will be upon him on the day he is raised alive"